/*
 * =============================================================================
 *  EV BIKE NODE  --  OPTION A  (ESP32-C3, STA mode -> Google Sheets DIRECT)
 * =============================================================================
 *
 *  This is the DEPLOYMENT path. The C3 joins your phone's hotspot (which has
 *  internet) and POSTs each sample straight to a Google Apps Script web app.
 *  The phone's browser is only used to view the dashboard and tap a bike;
 *  the LOGGING goes C3 -> internet -> Google with no phone involvement.
 *
 *  WHY STA:  In AP mode the C3 has no upstream internet, so it CANNOT reach
 *            Google. STA (join a hotspot) is the only way for the C3 itself
 *            to log to Sheets.
 *
 *  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 *  WIFI  --  NO WIRING. The C3 has WiFi on-chip (trace antenna on the board).
 *            You only set the SSID/PASS below. That's the whole "connection".
 *  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
 *
 *  GNSS WIRING  (Ebyte E108-GN03D, AT6558R, 9600 8N1 NMEA, 2.7-3.6V)
 *  -- C3 pins (SuperMini). NO level shifter: module is 3.3V native.
 *        GN03D  VCC  -> C3 3V3
 *        GN03D  GND  -> C3 GND
 *        GN03D  TXD  -> C3 GPIO4   (this sketch's GNSS RX)
 *        GN03D  RXD  -> C3 GPIO5   (optional; only if sending config)
 *     For an ACTIVE antenna, short the board's RF_POWER jumper.
 *
 *  PHONE HOTSPOT STEPS
 *     1. Phone: turn ON Personal Hotspot. Note its name + password.
 *     2. Put them in STA_SSID / STA_PASS below. Flash.
 *     3. Watch Serial -> it prints  "Dashboard: http://192.168.x.x"
 *        (NOT 192.168.4.1 -- that was AP mode). Open that URL in the phone.
 *     4. iPhone: keep the hotspot screen awake during first connect.
 *
 *  GOOGLE SHEETS  (one-time)
 *     - New Google Sheet -> Extensions -> Apps Script -> paste the script at
 *       the bottom of this file -> Deploy -> New deployment -> Web app ->
 *       Execute as: Me, Access: Anyone -> copy the /exec URL into GS_PATH.
 *
 *  BOARD: ESP32C3 Dev Module | USB CDC On Boot: Enabled | Partition: Huge APP
 *  LIB  : NimBLE-Arduino
 * =============================================================================
 */

